#### Bundled software included:

__[gpg4win-vanilla](https://chocolatey.org/packages/gpg4win-vanilla)__ includes:

* [GnuPG](https://www.gnupg.org/) -- The backend; this is the actual encryption tool ([GnuPG FAQ](https://www.gnupg.org/faq/gnupg-faq.html#general))

__[gpg4win-light](https://chocolatey.org/packages/gpg4win-light)__ includes all the above, and:

* [GPA](https://www.gnupg.org/related_software/gpa/index.html) -- An alternative certificate manager for OpenPGP and X.509 (S/MIME).
* [GpgOL](http://git.gnupg.org/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi?p=gpgol.git;a=summary) -- A plugin for the 32bit versions of Microsoft Outlook 2003/2007/2010/2013 (email encryption). For Outlook 2010/2013 GpgpOL supports the Exchange Server, but does not support MIME.
* [GpgEX](http://git.gnupg.org/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi?p=gpgex.git;a=summary) -- A plugin for Microsoft Explorer (file encryption).
* [Claws Mail](http://www.claws-mail.org/) -- A complete email application with crypto support.

__gpg4win__ (this package) includes all the above, and:

* [Kleopatra](https://www.kde.org/applications/utilities/kleopatra/) -- A certificate manager for OpenPGP and X.509 (S/MIME) and common crypto dialogs.
* [Compendium](http://www.gpg4win.org/doc/en/gpg4win-compendium.html) -- The documentation (for beginner and advanced users), available in English and German.
